history.content: There are very few CS-declared students so we reserved seats, but not many. They are still open, but I can't guarantee that they will still be open during your Phase II. Unfortunately, you will have to choose two classes that you want to prioritize over the 3rd.

Hi, I searched and I couldn't find anyone in the same situation.

I am a declared 2nd year L&S CS major. I really would like to take 16a next semester, but I need to use my phase 1 units on other classes (language classes). How likely am I to get in if I phase 2 it + how full are the reserved spots for 2nd year declared cs majors? (group 3 on this: https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/eecs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy#lower)

Phase 1: This Thursday, 9:30 am

Phase 2: Nov 29, 12:30 pm

Thanks a bunch!
